-- U.S. Official Welcomes Commitment of $430 Billion for IMF
-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 2012-04-20T21:51:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/u-s-official-welcomes-commitment-of-430-billion-for-imf.html
A U.S. official welcomed the more
than $430 billion in fresh money pledged to the  International
Monetary Fund  to help prevent the spread of the European debt
crisis.  The official, speaking in a briefing to reporters in
Washington today, called the additional funding a gesture of
solidarity with  Europe  and said the region still needs to remain
vigilant. The official declined to be identified
as a condition for giving the briefing.  To contact the reporters on this story:
